# CODEOWNERS — drives required-review routing for protected paths
#
# Format: <path-glob>  <owner-team-or-user>
# Each line is checked top-down; the LAST matching line wins. Order
# matters — broadest patterns first, specific overrides last.
#
# Tiers:
#   @techempower-org/owners       — Storyvox project leads. Admin everything.
#   @techempower-org/maintainers  — Merge rights + sensitive-path approval.
#   @techempower-org/contributors — Push to feature branches; protected by
#                                branch protection from merging own PRs.

# Default — every PR needs at least Maintainers review.
*  @techempower-org/maintainers

# ── Build & release surface — Maintainers ──────────────────────────────
# Version bumps, dep upgrades, gradle plugin changes. A botched edit here
# breaks every CI run and every release.
/app/build.gradle.kts           @techempower-org/maintainers
/gradle/libs.versions.toml      @techempower-org/maintainers
/settings.gradle.kts            @techempower-org/maintainers
/build.gradle.kts               @techempower-org/maintainers
/CHANGELOG.md                   @techempower-org/maintainers

# ── Sensitive / Owners-only ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Signing key, CI workflows, project-private rules. Compromise here means
# someone else can sign APKs with our cert, ship code on push to main, or
# rewrite the AI agent rules.
/app/storyvox-debug.keystore    @techempower-org/owners
/.github/workflows/             @techempower-org/owners
/.github/CODEOWNERS             @techempower-org/owners
/CLAUDE.md                      @techempower-org/owners

# ── Documentation — Maintainers ────────────────────────────────────────
/docs/                          @techempower-org/maintainers
/README.md                      @techempower-org/maintainers
